# Template drift allowlist for zudo-test-wisdom.
# Generated projects start from create-zudo-doc templates; this file lists
# intentional divergences from the pinned create-zudo-doc baseline so
# `pnpm check:template-drift` exits 0.
#
# Format: one repo-relative path per line (no leading slash).
# Blank lines and `#` comments are ignored.
#
# Every entry below maps to one of three reasons: a host customization, a
# feature intentionally left off, or a generated/runtime artifact. Reconciled
# for the zudo-doc 2.0.x "Collapse Wiring Shells" baseline (the per-component
# chrome shells + pages/_mdx-components.ts are gone; page chrome is wired via
# pages/lib/_chrome.ts, byte-identical to the template, so it is NOT listed).

# ── Generated / runtime artifact ──────────────────────────────────────────
# .zfb/ is gitignored; doc-history-meta.json is written at build time by the
# doc-history plugin and does not exist in the working tree.
.zfb/doc-history-meta.json

# ── Host customization: customized b4push gate ────────────────────────────
# scripts/run-b4push.sh is the full 8-step gate (format + drift + pin-parity +
# wrangler-pin + check + build + html + links), replacing the template default.
scripts/run-b4push.sh

# ── Host customization: resolved compose @slot markers ────────────────────
# The base template ships @slot: injection markers so the compose framework can
# inject feature-specific code at scaffold time. Production has these slots
# resolved (removed) and the real implementations inlined for this site's
# enabled features (imageEnlarge, docHistory, etc.).
pages/lib/_body-end-islands.tsx
src/config/settings-types.ts
src/styles/global.css

# ── Feature island shims (base no-op stub vs. feature re-export shim) ──────
# The base template ships no-op W6A stubs for these island components so imports
# resolve in a feature-off scaffold. This site enables the corresponding
# features (sidebarToggle / docHistory / imageEnlarge), so it ships the feature
# template's thin re-export shim pointing at the package island, which the drift
# check flags against the base-template stub.
src/components/desktop-sidebar-toggle.tsx
src/components/doc-history.tsx
src/components/image-enlarge.tsx

# ── Host customization: brand typography (Futura) ─────────────────────────
# The homepage title <h1> elements carry the `font-futura` utility + `font-normal`
# to restore the pre-zfb site's normal-weight Futura titles (the base template
# ships `font-bold`). The `--font-futura` token + the header `[data-header-logo]`
# rule live in the already-allowlisted src/styles/global.css. (The doc-page title
# h1 now lives in package-owned chrome — its former host shells
# _doc-content-header / _doc-page-shell were removed in the 2.0.x collapse.)
pages/index.tsx
pages/[locale]/index.tsx

# ── Feature intentionally OFF: docTags / tagGovernance ────────────────────
# docTags is `false` and tagGovernance is `off` in settings.ts. The docTags /
# tagGovernance feature templates ship these files, but this site does not
# scaffold them. The tag data model + frontmatter field are kept for future use;
# the tag pages and audit scripts are intentionally absent. (The tags *routes*
# themselves are package-owned under packageOwnedRoutes, so no page stubs exist.)
pages/lib/_tag-pages.tsx
scripts/tags-audit.ts
scripts/tags-suggest.ts
